renormalization scheme independent, and intrinsically
geometric.


3. Some Examples 
We shall now argue, with examples, that many of the
widely accepted properties of the RG flow do not exclude
strange attractors from appearing in the IR limit of the
flow. We start by considering examples of field theoretical
RG coupling flow equations from the perspective
of the -theorems.

An important example of a RG coupling flow
with three independent couplings (the minimal
number required for a chaotic flow) is the
 standard model in
four dimensions. At the two-loop level, and ignoring
the contribution from the Higgs sector, the three gauge
couplings  flow according tot^i  =  g^ij  _j F
